.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_InteractableObject
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Interactable Object script is attached to any game object that is required to be interacted with (e.g. via the controllers).
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks:
The basis of this script is to provide a simple mechanism for identifying objects in the game world that can be grabbed or used but it is expected that this script is the base to be inherited into a script with richer functionality.

 The highlighting of an Interactable Object is defaulted to use the `VRTK_MaterialColorSwapHighlighter` if no other highlighter is applied to the Object.
.NET Framework 3.5.example:
VRTK/Examples/005_Controller_BasicObjectGrabbing uses the VRTK_InteractTouch and VRTK_InteractGrab scripts on the controllers to show how an interactable object can be grabbed and snapped to the controller and thrown around the game world.

 `VRTK/Examples/013_Controller_UsingAndGrabbingMultipleObjects` shows multiple objects that can be grabbed by holding the buttons or grabbed by toggling the button click and also has objects that can have their Using state toggled to show how multiple items can be turned on at the same time.

ForceStopInteracting()
methods.summary: The ForceStopInteracting method forces the object to no longer be interacted with and will cause a controller to drop the object and stop touching it. This is useful if the controller is required to auto interact with another object.

methods.name: ForceStopSecondaryGrabInteraction()
methods.summary: The ForceStopSecondaryGrabInteraction method forces the object to no longer be influenced by the second controller grabbing it.

methods.name: GetGrabbingObject()
methods.summary: The GetGrabbingObject method is used to return the game object that is currently grabbing this object.
methods.returns: The game object of what is grabbing the current object.

methods.name: GetSecondaryGrabbingObject()
methods.summary: The GetSecondaryGrabbingObject method is used to return the game object that is currently being used to influence this object whilst it is being grabbed by a secondary controller.
methods.returns: The game object of the secondary controller influencing the current grabbed object.

methods.name: GetStoredSnapDropZone()

methods.returns: The SnapDropZone that the interactable object is currently snapped to.

methods.name: GetTouchingObjects()
methods.summary: The GetTouchingObjects method is used to return the collecetion of valid game objects that are currently touching this object.
methods.returns: A list of game object of that are currently touching the current object.

methods.name: GetUsingObject()
methods.summary: The GetUsingObject method is used to return the GameObject that is currently using this object.
methods.returns: The GameObject of what is using the current object.

methods.name: GetUsingScript()

methods.returns: The InteractUse script of the object that is using the current object.

methods.name: IsDroppable()
methods.summary: The IsDroppable method returns whether the object can be dropped or not in it's current situation.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object can currently be dropped and returns false if it is not currently possible to drop.

methods.name: IsGrabbed(GameObject grabbedBy)
methods.summary: The IsGrabbed method is used to determine if the object is currently being grabbed.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object is currently being grabbed.

params.value: An optional GameObject to check if the Interactable Object is grabbed by that specific GameObject. Defaults to null

methods.name: IsInSnapDropZone()
methods.summary: The IsInSnapDropZone method determines whether the interactable object is currently snapped to a drop zone.
methods.returns: Returns true if the interactable object is currently snapped in a drop zone and returns false if it is not.

methods.name: IsSwappable()
methods.summary: The IsSwappable method returns whether the object can be grabbed with one controller and then swapped to another controller by grabbing with the secondary controller.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object can be grabbed by a secondary controller whilst already being grabbed and the object will swap controllers. Returns false if the object cannot be swapped.

methods.name: IsTouched()
methods.summary: The IsTouched method is used to determine if the object is currently being touched.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object is currently being touched.

methods.name: IsUsing(GameObject usedBy)
methods.summary: The IsUsing method is used to determine if the object is currently being used.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object is currently being used.

params.value: An optional GameObject to check if the Interactable Object is used by that specific GameObject. Defaults to null

methods.name: IsValidInteractableController(GameObject actualController, AllowedController controllerCheck)
methods.summary: The IsValidInteractableController method is used to check to see if a controller is allowed to perform an interaction with this object as sometimes controllers are prohibited from grabbing or using an object depedning on the use case.
methods.returns: Is true if the interacting controller is allowed to grab the object.

params.value: The game object of the controller that is being checked.
The value of which controller is allowed to interact with this object.

methods.name: PauseCollisions(float delay)
methods.summary: The PauseCollisions method temporarily pauses all collisions on the object at grab time by removing the object's rigidbody's ability to detect collisions. This can be useful for preventing clipping when initially grabbing an item.

params.value: The amount of time to pause the collisions for.

methods.name: PerformSecondaryAction()
methods.summary: The PerformSecondaryAction method returns whether the object has a secondary action that can be performed when grabbing the object with a secondary controller.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object has a secondary action, returns false if it has no secondary action or is swappable.
